               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Ostracon, fragment of the rim of a fine buff-coloured pottery bowl with flaring sides and turned rim, both interior and exterior covered with an orange-red burnished slip, with remains of four lines of Coptic text written in black ink on the interior and another line on the exterior, containing a table of fractions.</note>
                     <note type="general">Writing on both sides.</note>
                     <note type="lines">Remains of five lines of Coptic text written in black ink: interior - faint traces of one line and a further three lines of text, separated by a drawn line; exterior - faint traces of one line of text.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="egy-Copt">Coptic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
